chunk_content: For example, if an individual had received prevention P R interventions under PP_PREV through PEPFAR-supported program in January 2017 and was counted E as being reached in FY17 Q2 reporting cycle, and this same individual was later reached with V prevention services again by PEPFAR-supported program in June 2017, that individual should NOT be E N reported again in the FY17 Q4 reporting period. This de-duplication is critical to accurately track the T ANNUAL number of unique individuals reached by PEPFAR within a given fiscal year. Trend analysis of I O past performance PP_PREV data will be adversely affected with the change in frequency of PP_PREV N reporting from annually to semi-annually if this de-duplication is ignored (i.e., annual number of PP_PREV reported within the same fiscal year would be inflated as the same individual would be counted twice if this de-duplication does not occur at Q4 reporting).
